Mail is no longer Metal.

00:38:09.120 --> 00:38:12.040
Mail is a real standard Aqua application.

00:38:13.590 --> 00:38:17.700
For example, so layout and appearance,
what are the best practices for this

00:38:17.700 --> 00:38:19.670
area of the design of your product?

00:38:19.740 --> 00:38:21.640
Focus on clean design.

00:38:21.640 --> 00:38:23.100
It really matters.

00:38:23.100 --> 00:38:26.570
From the get-go,
when I open the package and start

00:38:26.640 --> 00:38:30.020
running the piece of software,
now I'm, you know, I mean,

00:38:30.020 --> 00:38:32.750
this is my job,
so I look at this kind of stuff,

00:38:32.750 --> 00:38:36.050
but products that are messy,
that have a cluttered UI,

00:38:36.050 --> 00:38:39.640
and that are poorly designed visually,
make me feel like the

00:38:39.640 --> 00:38:43.480
code quality is of equal,
like the code is of equal quality.

00:38:43.500 --> 00:38:47.490
Don't get your code judged based on
the appearance of the application.

00:38:47.490 --> 00:38:49.430
It's like anything in our world, right?

00:38:49.490 --> 00:38:52.210
We buy anything,
and if it looks crummy or it, you know,

00:38:52.390 --> 00:38:55.260
doesn't look high quality,
then we start to wonder whether

00:38:55.260 --> 00:38:58.250
the product actually does what
the vendor is claiming it does.

00:38:58.260 --> 00:39:00.710
Follow the Aqua layout guidelines.

00:39:00.740 --> 00:39:02.580
We don't publish these
numbers for nothing.

00:39:02.580 --> 00:39:04.550
We've thought long and
hard about these things.

00:39:04.550 --> 00:39:07.710
