00:43:22.880 --> 00:43:23.400
One more thing.

00:43:24.740 --> 00:43:27.590
on the cross-platform topic,
file name extensions.

00:43:27.690 --> 00:43:30.840
Great way to ensure
compatibility between files,

00:43:30.870 --> 00:43:32.440
between multiple OSs, right?

00:43:32.480 --> 00:43:35.640
Users in heterogeneous environments
are moving documents back and forth.

00:43:35.670 --> 00:43:38.550
Mac OS X fits into that
world a whole lot better than

00:43:38.550 --> 00:43:40.760
earlier versions of Mac OS did.

00:43:42.820 --> 00:43:44.020
What does that mean for you,
the developer?

00:43:44.020 --> 00:43:45.290
A couple things.

00:43:45.290 --> 00:43:51.320
First of all, the save panel has a hide
extension checkbox that the

00:43:51.320 --> 00:43:52.660
system provides for you.

00:43:52.660 --> 00:43:55.750
Make sure you're taking
advantage of launch services

00:43:55.830 --> 00:43:57.520
APIs to do the right thing.

00:43:57.520 --> 00:44:00.970
The system will set or hide that
checkbox based on what the user types.

00:44:01.060 --> 00:44:04.710
Basically, the rule for file name
extensions in Mac OS X is

00:44:05.050 --> 00:44:06.840
what you type is what you see.

00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:09.220
If you type an extension,
you'll see an extension.

00:44:09.380 --> 00:44:12.670
If you don't type an extension,
you'll never see that extension.

00:44:12.700 --> 00:44:14.300
to file extension, okay?

00:44:14.300 --> 00:44:16.860
And it's on a per file basis.

00:44:16.940 --> 00:44:21.460
So, as a result of that,
the choice is in the user's hand.

00:44:21.460 --> 00:44:24.850
Therefore,
make sure that you show the proper

00:44:24.920 --> 00:44:31.210
display name for a file in your UI,
whether it's the document title,

00:44:31.530 --> 00:44:35.210
or whether it's some, you know, status,
dialog box that shows status

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:37.840
or information about a
document or what have you,

00:44:37.870 --> 00:44:40.320
anything,
any UI that shows information about a

00:44:40.320 --> 00:44:43.200
document should show the display name.

00:44:43.220 --> 00:44:45.920
There's a set of APIs in
Mac OS X called Launch Services,

00:44:45.920 --> 00:44:50.250
and you can say, "Hey, Launch Services,
with this file system object, you know,

00:44:50.340 --> 00:44:53.880
file on system, what's its display name?"
And Launch Services will know whether

00:44:54.240 --> 00:44:57.740
the extension should be shown or not,
and just pass you the right string back.

00:44:57.820 --> 00:45:01.420
So here's a file that
has no extension on it,

00:45:01.450 --> 00:45:04.000
or at least that's not visible,
and here's the same file with

00:45:04.000 --> 00:45:05.080
the extension being shown.

00:45:05.080 --> 00:45:07.320
So the user typed it one way or
the user typed it the other way.

00:45:07.320 --> 00:45:12.070
Make sure your application respects that,
because that's what the user wanted.

00:45:13.000 --> 00:45:15.920
So best practices for
cross-platform design,

00:45:15.930 --> 00:45:17.220
a lot of things.

00:45:17.230 --> 00:45:19.520
Be consistent, yet platform adaptive.

00:45:19.520 --> 00:45:25.780
So what users really want is the same
functionality in the same locations,

00:45:25.780 --> 00:45:29.900
but they want the system appearance from
the platform that they're running on.

00:45:29.900 --> 00:45:32.690
So in other words,
it's not that they want the pref panel,

00:45:32.690 --> 00:45:35.020
the preferences dialog,
to look exactly like it

00:45:35.020 --> 00:45:36.640
does on some other platform.

00:45:36.640 --> 00:45:39.990
They want the same options to be
available in the preference dialog,

00:45:39.990 --> 00:45:42.060
and they want them to
be in the same tabs,

00:45:42.060 --> 00:45:42.760
for example.

00:45:42.900 --> 00:45:43.930
Thank you.

00:45:44.520 --> 00:45:48.180
Provide identical functionality
between the platforms.

00:45:48.260 --> 00:45:50.480
Don't deliver an inferior
product on Mac OS X.

00:45:50.480 --> 00:45:54.450
There's stuff available in Mac OS X now
that can enable you to take your

00:45:54.450 --> 00:45:58.260
product to a whole new level in
terms of overall functionality and

00:45:58.390 --> 00:46:01.550
connectivity and user experience.

00:46:02.110 --> 00:46:04.560
Deliver the
platform-appropriate appearance.

00:46:04.600 --> 00:46:06.650
Make sure you're leveraging
standard system controls,

00:46:06.650 --> 00:46:08.980
right, to get the Aqua appearance,
look and feel.

00:46:08.980 --> 00:46:10.880
Platform behaviors.

00:46:10.880 --> 00:46:12.820
For example, drag and drop.

00:46:12.890 --> 00:46:15.880
Drag and drop on
Mac OS works a certain way.

00:46:15.880 --> 00:46:18.310
Make sure that your application
fits into that world and it

00:46:18.310 --> 00:46:21.730
accepts a drag from the desktop,
if that's appropriate for it to do that,

00:46:21.730 --> 00:46:23.560
given the workflow users might have.

00:46:23.610 --> 00:46:25.100
Leverage platform strengths.

00:46:25.100 --> 00:46:27.390
Wherever possible,
take advantage of really cool

00:46:27.390 --> 00:46:28.740
technologies on Mac OS X.

00:46:28.740 --> 00:46:31.010
Some of them don't relate
to user experience,

00:46:31.090 --> 00:46:31.840
but many do.

00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:36.970
If you're in education, higher ed,
there's some good reasons for using text.

00:46:37.060 --> 00:46:43.660
We have a great synthesizer on
Mac OS X that can speak back text

00:46:43.660 --> 00:46:48.630
and save your application from
having to store digital audio.

00:46:48.640 --> 00:46:50.710
You can reduce the size
of your footprint on a CD,

00:46:50.710 --> 00:46:53.620
for example, and speak back text in a
very intelligible voice.

00:46:53.640 --> 00:46:55.350
There are other technologies.

00:46:55.350 --> 00:46:56.170
Address book.

00:46:56.220 --> 00:46:59.560
Don't write your own, you know,
contact management system.

00:46:59.630 --> 00:47:00.640
Leverage address book.

00:47:00.640 --> 00:47:01.920
So leverage the relevant technologies.

00:47:01.920 --> 00:47:07.590
Embrace file name extensions
and show the display name.

00:47:07.910 --> 00:47:10.570
And lastly,
avoid delivering a lowest common

00:47:10.570 --> 00:47:11.950
denominator user experience.

00:47:11.990 --> 00:47:16.720
The problem that I see in many cases with
cross-platform applications is they're

00:47:16.720 --> 00:47:18.630
not leveraging platform strengths.

00:47:18.740 --> 00:47:22.960
And yeah, I'm standing up here for Apple,
encouraging you to leverage

00:47:23.060 --> 00:47:27.280
platform strengths from Mac OS X,
but the same is true for Windows,

00:47:27.290 --> 00:47:30.100
if you're delivering on Mac and Windows.

00:47:30.100 --> 00:47:33.380
If you deliver a lowest common
denominator user experience,

00:47:33.380 --> 00:47:36.060
your Windows users are
going to suffer as well.

00:47:37.040 --> 00:47:39.550
